  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off High regime, but the critical override is USD H4 CSM fading hard to 44 versus D1 at 100, a 56-point divergence that is the single most important short-term signal in this brief. USDCAD D1+H4 strong buy with CMP 67 remains the cleanest USD expression, while AUDUSD and NZDUSD H4 CSM acceleration to 70 and 62 respectively, confirmed by AUDJPY correlation at 0.91 and NZDJPY at 0.92, signal intraday counter-pressure building in commodity pairs.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: GBPJPY CMP 53 with H4 momentum 64 accelerating, NZDJPY CMP 56 H4 60 pushing higher\nFading: EURUSD CMP 40 D1 momentum 32 declining, GBPUSD CMP 43 D1 momentum 29 declining\n\nWATCH\nUK Retail Sales disappointment sustains GBPUSD sell pressure on any D1 momentum rebound toward the H4 neutral zone, confirming downside continuation.\nWTI at 98.95 up 2.7 percent conflicts directly with US-Iran deal optimism; a confirmed oil reversal lower fires CADJPY sell given H4 strong sell signal already active.\nCHF H4 CSM at 100 versus D1 at 33 marks the largest accelerating divergence; USDCHF H4 fading momentum at 56 signals a short entry setup on a pullback.",
